{"type":"message","id":"0df1c609","parentId":"5987085e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:19:35.647Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g7hmu2k0ky1i_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 131814\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. The CFI Compression experiment was just completed (2026-03-24)\r\n3. Key finding: need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter with CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n4. Next experiment listed: \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. This would implement the scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and what needs to be done. I need to:\r\n1. Create or modify an experiment script that tests the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Use the existing pulse data to run this experiment\r\n\r\nLooking at the research folder, there should be pulse data available. Let me check what exists.\r\n\r\nActually, I should create the experiment that tests the hybrid scoring approach. This would be a new document or script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Applies the hybrid scoring: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n3. Tests against the same 200-pulse dataset\r\n4. Compares with previous results\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action - I'll write a Python script or analysis document for the hybrid experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression experiment identified the need for a hybrid scoring approach, but hasn't implemented and tested it yet. The formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) is concrete and testable against the existing 200-pulse dataset.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python experiment script to test the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring strategy against the existing pulse data, providing empirical validation for Strategy C before implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n## Strategy C Validation (2026-03-24)\r\n\r\n## Scoring Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\n| Token Type | CFI | freq | score | Include? |\r\n|------------|-----|------|-------|----------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.00×1.0 = 1.00 | FILTERED (freq≥120) |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | 0.96×1.0 = 0.96 | FILTERED (freq≥120) |\r\n| \"temporal\" | 0.72 | 45 | 0.72×0.375 = 0.27 | CANDIDATE |\r\n| \"compression\" | 0.65 | 23 | 0.65×0.192 = 0.12 | CANDIDATE |\r\n| \"Architecture\" | 0.55 | 8 | 0.55×0.067 = 0.037 | WEAK |\r\n| \"breakaway\" | 0.45 | 5 | 0.45×0.042 = 0.019 | WEAK |\r\n| \"discontinuity\" | 0.30 | 3 | 0.30×0.025 = 0.008 | EXCLUDE |\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- [ ] Load existing 200-pulse dataset\r\n- [ ] Compute hybrid scores for all tokens\r\n- [ ] Test threshold values: 0.1, 0.15, 0.20\r\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall vs Strategy A (freq-only) and Strategy B (CFI-only)\r\n- [ ] Identify optimal threshold empirically\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nFilter out high-frequency constants (CFI=1, freq=160) while preserving research tokens (CFI>0.5, freq<120).\r\n```\r\nfile: research/hybrid_cfi_freq_experiment.py\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:18:30\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372775645}}
{"type":"message","id":"bedf4f66","parentId":"0df1c609","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:19:43.160Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the pulse log and the pulse script has completed. Let me summarize what happened in this pulse cycle.\n\nThe pulse log shows:\n- Phase 0 (CFI Compression experiment) completed\n- Phase 1 (Synthesis) completed  \n- Generated 1 mutation proposal (the hybrid scoring experiment)\n- Current state: hybrid experiment pending, next action to create the experiment\n\nLet me write this to today's memory file.","thinkingSignature":"34c07fb317775596aa740cf8200b1c6ffe547590e7871b5b449b6b5e9fe73999"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 13:18**\n\n**Completed:**\n- **Phase 0:** CFI Compression experiment — confirmed that the original 10-token \"core vocabulary\" (CFI=1.0) is a compression artifact. Tokens like `\"for next instantiation\"` (freq=160) and `\"Phase 1\"` (freq=136) are high-frequency boilerplate, not true abstractions.\n- **Phase 1:** Synthesis — identified that a pure frequency filter (≤120 Hz) alone is insufficient; it wrongly excludes valid research tokens with freq<120. The key insight: **need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter** with CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120).\n\n**Mutation Proposed (1):**\n- Create `research/hybrid_cfi_freq_experiment.py` to test a hybrid scoring formula: `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` against the 200-pulse dataset. This would empirically validate Strategy C before implementing it in the actual codebase.\n\n**Status:** Ready for next instantiation."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1417,"output":317,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13871,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774372775648}}
